.\" Manpage for pkmgr
.TH man 1 "08 May 2026" "202606040901-git" "pkmgr"

.SH NAME
pkmgr \- Universal package manager wrapper for multiple Linux distributions

.SH DESCRIPTION
A unified package management utility that provides a consistent interface across different Linux distributions and package managers. Supports apt/apt-get, dnf/yum, tdnf, pacman/pamac/yay, apk, xbps, brew, and language-specific package managers (pip, gem, npm, cpan, lua, go).

.SH SYNOPSIS
pkmgr [options] [command] [arguments...]

.SH BASIC COMMANDS
.TP
.B search <package>
Search for a package in repositories
.TP
.B install <package>
Install one or more packages
.TP
.B install fix
Fix broken package installations (dpkg --configure, apt -f install, dnf distro-sync, etc.)
.TP
.B remove <package>
Remove installed package
.TP
.B update
Update all installed packages
.TP
.B upgrade
Alias for update
.TP
.B clean
Remove cached package files
.TP
.B makecache
Update package repository lists
.TP
.B init
Initialize system: clean cache, refresh repos, and upgrade packages
.TP
.B list <file>
Install packages from a list file
.TP
.B reinstall
Reinstall all packages tracked by pkmgr
.TP
.B silent install <package>
Silently install package without prompts
.TP
.B silent remove <package>
Silently remove package
.TP
.B silent upgrade
Silently upgrade all packages

.SH ADVANCED COMMANDS
.TP
.B info
Show system and package manager information
.TP
.B bin [args...]
Pass arguments directly to the underlying package manager binary
.TP
.B check
Check for available updates
.TP
.B available
List available packages
.TP
.B export
Export list of installed packages
.TP
.B import <file>
Install packages from an exported list file
.TP
.B dotfiles [type]
Install required packages for dotfiles (e.g., pkmgr dotfiles git)
.TP
.B curl <distro> <type>
Install packages from URL-based list (e.g., pkmgr curl debian min)
.TP
.B script <path|url>
Run installation script from local path or URL
.TP
.B cron add
Schedule automatic daily package updates
.TP
.B cron remove
Remove scheduled automatic updates
.TP
.B cron run
Run the cron update task immediately
.TP
.B aliases
List and optionally save bash aliases for package management
.TP
.B required <package>
Install a required package (used internally by other scripts)

.SH KEY MANAGEMENT COMMANDS
.TP
.B keys broken
Attempt to fix broken or expired package signing keys
.TP
.B keys remove
Remove all package signing keys
.TP
.B keys init
Initialize package signing keys from scratch
.TP
.B keys update
Update existing package signing keys
.TP
.B keys reinstall
Reinstall the distribution keyring package(s)
.TP
.B keys wtf
Temporarily disable all package signature verification to allow installation; re-enables afterward

.SH LANGUAGE-SPECIFIC PACKAGE MANAGERS
.TP
.B pip <package>
Install Python package via pip
.TP
.B cpan <module>
Install Perl module via CPAN (e.g., pkmgr cpan Bundle::Apache)
.TP
.B gem <gem>
Install Ruby gem (e.g., pkmgr gem jekyll)
.TP
.B npm <package>
Install Node.js package via npm (e.g., pkmgr npm express)
.TP
.B lua <module>
Install Lua rock via luarocks
.TP
.B go <module>
Install Go module via go get

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --help
Display help message
.TP
.B --version
Show script version
.TP
.B --config
Generate user configuration file
.TP
.B --options
Show all available options
.TP
.B --debug
Enable debugging output
.TP
.B --no-color
Remove formatting from output
.TP
.B --force
Force package installation/operation
.TP
.B --silent
Suppress non-essential output
.TP
.B --enable-log
Enable logging of package operations to the log directory
.TP
.B --enable-aur
Enable AUR (Arch User Repository) support on Arch-based systems

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B pkmgr search vim
Search for vim package
.TP
.B pkmgr install vim neovim git
Install multiple packages
.TP
.B pkmgr install fix
Fix broken package state
.TP
.B pkmgr remove apache2
Remove Apache web server
.TP
.B pkmgr update
Update all system packages
.TP
.B pkmgr clean
Clean package cache
.TP
.B pkmgr list /path/to/packages.txt
Install all packages listed in file
.TP
.B pkmgr dotfiles git
Install git-related dotfiles packages
.TP
.B pkmgr curl debian min
Install minimal Debian packages from URL list
.TP
.B pkmgr silent install nginx
Silently install nginx without prompts
.TP
.B pkmgr pip requests beautifulsoup4
Install Python packages
.TP
.B pkmgr npm express socket.io
Install Node.js packages
.TP
.B pkmgr gem rails bundler
Install Ruby gems
.TP
.B pkmgr cron add
Enable automatic daily package updates
.TP
.B pkmgr keys broken
Attempt to fix broken/expired signing keys
.TP
.B pkmgr keys wtf
Temporarily disable signature verification for a single update
.TP
.B pkmgr info
Display system and package manager information
.TP
.B pkmgr bin --version
Run the underlying package manager with --version

.SH SUPPORTED PACKAGE MANAGERS
pkmgr automatically detects and uses the appropriate package manager:

.SS Linux Distribution Managers
.TP
.B apt/apt-get
Debian, Ubuntu, Linux Mint, Pop!_OS, and derivatives
.TP
.B dnf/yum
Fedora, RHEL, CentOS, Rocky Linux, AlmaLinux
.TP
.B tdnf
VMware Photon OS
.TP
.B pacman
Arch Linux, EndeavourOS, CachyOS, ArcoLinux, Artix
.TP
.B pamac
Manjaro Linux
.TP
.B yay
Arch-based systems with AUR support (via --enable-aur)
.TP
.B apk
Alpine Linux
.TP
.B xbps
Void Linux
.TP
.B brew
macOS, Linux (Homebrew)
.TP
.B choco
Windows (Chocolatey)

.SS Language Package Managers
.TP
.B pip/pip3
Python packages
.TP
.B cpan
Perl modules
.TP
.B gem
Ruby gems
.TP
.B npm
Node.js packages
.TP
.B go get
Go modules
.TP
.B luarocks
Lua modules

.SH CONFIGURATION
.TP
.B Auto-Detection
Automatically detects the system package manager at startup
.TP
.B Sudo Handling
Automatically uses sudo when required for system-level operations
.TP
.B AUR Support
Enable AUR support on Arch-based systems with --enable-aur; uses yay if available

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/myscripts/pkmgr/settings.conf
User configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.local/log/pkmgr/
Log directory for package operations (when --enable-log is active)
.TP
.I ~/.cache/pkmgr/
Cache directory
.TP
.I /usr/local/etc/pkmgr/lists/
Installed package tracking directory

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B PKMGR_CONFIG_DIR
Configuration directory (default: ~/.config/myscripts/pkmgr)
.TP
.B PKMGR_REQUIRE_SUDO
Whether sudo is required (auto-detected)
.TP
.B PKMGR_FORCE
Force operations without prompts
.TP
.B PKMGR_LOG_ENABLED
Set to "true" to enable operation logging (also set by --enable-log)
.TP
.B PKMGR_GIT_REPO
Remote repository URL used by dotfiles and curl commands
.TP
.B PKMGR_GIT_BRANCH
Branch to use for remote package lists (default: main)

.SH NOTES
pkmgr provides a unified interface across different Linux distributions, eliminating the need to remember distribution-specific package manager commands.

The tool automatically handles sudo requirements based on the operation and system configuration.

Silent mode (silent command) is useful for automation and scripting where interactive prompts should be avoided.

Rolling release distributions (Arch, Void, openSUSE Tumbleweed, etc.) display "rolling" as their version in pkmgr info output.

.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Distribution package manager
apt, dnf, pacman, apk, xbps, etc. (auto-detected)
.TP
.B sudo
For system-level package operations
.TP
.B curl/wget
For URL-based package lists

